# No Direct Force Push to responsum-team/dbtproject

NEVER run `git push --force` (or `git push -f`) directly to `responsum-team/dbtproject` from the main repo (`elixirrjob1/cursorskills`).

The only approved way to update `responsum-team/dbtproject` is through the temp-clone sync process:

```bash
source .env
rm -rf /tmp/dbt-push-tmp
git clone https://github.com/elixirrjob1/cursorskills.git /tmp/dbt-push-tmp
cd /tmp/dbt-push-tmp
git filter-repo --subdirectory-filter dbt_project/drip_transformations --force
git remote add dbt-remote "https://${PAT2}@github.com/responsum-team/dbtproject.git"
git push dbt-remote main:main --force
```

This ensures `dbt_project.yml` lands at the root of the secondary repo (required by dbt Cloud).

A direct force push from the main repo would push the full `elixirrjob1/cursorskills` tree — overwriting the secondary repo with unrelated files (skills, scripts, .env, etc.).
